    {
      "question": "From a point $P$, $10$ cm away from the centre of a circle, the length of the tangent drawn to the circle is $8$ cm. Find the radius of the circle.",
      "answer": "$6$ cm",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the property that the tangent is perpendicular to the radius at the point of contact.",
          "Apply Pythagoras theorem in the right-angled triangle formed by the radius, tangent, and the line from the centre to $P$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$r^2 + 8^2 = 10^2 \\\\ r^2 + 64 = 100 \\\\ r^2 = 36 \\\\ r = 6 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
