      "question": "Two concentric circles are of radii $5$ cm and $3$ cm. Find the length of the chord of the larger circle which touches the smaller circle.",
      "answer": "$8$ cm",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let $O$ be the centre, $AB$ be the chord of the larger circle tangent to the smaller circle at $M$.",
          "In $\\triangle OMA$, use Pythagoras theorem to find $AM$, then $AB = 2 \\times AM$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$OM = 3, \\ OA = 5 \\\\ AM = \\sqrt{5^2 - 3^2} = \\sqrt{25 - 9} = 4 \\\\ AB = 2 \\times 4 = 8 \\text{ cm}$"
      },
