    {
      "question": "If tangents $PA$ and $PB$ from a point $P$ to a circle with centre $O$ are inclined to each other at an angle of $80^\\circ$, find $\\angle POA$.",
      "answer": "$50^\\circ$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The line $OP$ bisects the angle $\\angle APB$. Thus $\\angle APO = 40^\\circ$.",
          "In $\\triangle OAP$, $\\angle OAP = 90^\\circ$. Therefore $\\angle POA = 90^\\circ - 40^\\circ$."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\angle APB = 80^\\circ \\Rightarrow \\angle APO = 40^\\circ \\\\ \\angle OAP = 90^\\circ \\\\ \\angle POA = 180^\\circ - 90^\\circ - 40^\\circ = 50^\\circ"
      },
